public abstract class WrappedDataWriter<WRAPPER extends KijiDataWrapper<DATUM>,DATUM>
extends KijiDataWriter

Base class for writers of Kiji data writers that use a wrapper to aid with encapsulating and buffering data.

                     Object value)
              throws IOException,
                     InterruptedException
Writes a value at the current timestamp and reports progress.

All other write methods of Kiji data writers delegate to this method. Subclasses should override this method to implement desired write functionality.

Specified by:
write in class KijiDataWriter
Parameters:
id - The entity id of the row to write to.
family - The family to write to.
qualifier - The key (column qualifier) to write the data to.
schema - The writer schema for the value.
timestamp - The timestamp at which the data will be written.
value - The data payload.
Throws:
IOException - If there is a problem writing.
InterruptedException - If the thread is interrupted while writing.
